        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>Egyptian pottery styles [300107283], Egyptian (ancient) [300020251], Mediterranean (Early Western World) [300020058], Early Western World [300019255], styles, periods, and cultures by region [300111079], Styles and Periods (hierarchy name) [300015646], Styles and Periods Facet [300264088]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the Egyptian pottery style produced during the Badarian period from about 6000 to 4000 BCE. The style is characterized by vessels with a ripple-burnished surface achieved by combing ripples into wet clay or rubbing a pebble over hard clay and then burnishing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de cerámica egipcio producido durante el período Badariense desde aproximadamente el 6000 al 4000 a.C. El estilo se caracteriza por vasos con una superficie pulida ondeada lograda peinando ondas en la arcilla húmeda o frotando un guijarro encima de la arcilla dura y puliendo después.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de Egyptische aardewerkstijl die werd vervaardigd tijdens de badarische periode van circa 6.000 tot 4.000 v. Chr. De stijl kenmerkt zich door een rimpelig gepolijst oppervlak, dat werd verkregen door rimpels in de natte klei te kammen of door met een kiezel over harde klei te wrijven en vervolgens te polijsten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052476/Allard Pierson Museum</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指自西元前6000年至西元前4000年間，於巴達爾時代生產的埃及陶器風格。其特色是藉由在濕土上梳刮出波紋，或在堅硬表面上以卵石摩擦製造出紋路，最後再打磨拋光而造成拋光波紋表面的陶器器皿。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
